## Follow-up: Upstream Issue

File an issue at https://github.com/getsentry/sentry-api-schema/ requesting that the OpenAPI spec for `retrieveAnIssue` (`GET /api/0/organizations/{org}/issues/{issue_id}/`) and `resolveAShortId` (`GET /api/0/organizations/{org}/shortids/{short_id}/`) declare the `collapse` query parameter (same type as on `listAnOrganizationSissues`). This would let SDK consumers pass `collapse` without switching to raw requests.

Key points for the issue:
- Both endpoints accept `collapse` at the server level (same Django view base class as the list endpoint)
- The OpenAPI spec has `query?: never` for both, so the generated `@sentry/api` SDK blocks query params
- The list endpoint (`listAnOrganizationSissues`) already declares `collapse` with values: `stats`, `lifetime`, `filtered`, `unhandled`, `base`
- The Sentry web UI already skips stats on issue detail to save 100-300ms
- SDK consumers currently must drop down to raw HTTP requests to pass `collapse` on detail endpoints
